WEBVTT

00:02.580 --> 00:06.750
♪♪

00:06.750 --> 00:10.460
Meredith: Since our hospital
is a teaching program,

00:10.460 --> 00:13.210
many of our patients allow
their surgeries to be filmed.

00:15.250 --> 00:17.170
♪ He is more real than myself ♪

00:17.170 --> 00:19.210
It's great as a teaching tool.

00:21.250 --> 00:23.710
But if you screw up,

00:23.710 --> 00:26.290
it ends up online for
the whole world to see.

00:26.290 --> 00:27.420
[ Sirens wailing ]

00:27.420 --> 00:29.380
Your mistakes will
be scrutinized,

00:29.380 --> 00:33.000
analyzed, studied,
written about...

00:33.000 --> 00:35.620
Richard's plane should
be landing soon. You should go.

00:35.620 --> 00:37.670
...argued over...
We have patients.
You sure?

00:37.670 --> 00:39.580
You came for a tour.
You ended up working overnight.

00:39.580 --> 00:41.670
Hold up, fellas.

00:41.670 --> 00:43.580
You deserve the break, man.
Go be there for your mom.

00:43.580 --> 00:44.920
And Miranda.

00:44.920 --> 00:47.380
I hear you.
Let me finish with this burn.

00:47.380 --> 00:49.920
...watched and re-watched.

00:49.920 --> 00:52.000
♪♪

00:52.000 --> 00:54.750
♪ Did he take me ♪

00:54.750 --> 00:56.250
We all make mistakes.

00:56.250 --> 00:58.330
We all have moments when
we weren't the best surgeon

00:58.330 --> 00:59.830
Okay.
or even the best person.

00:59.830 --> 01:01.750
Carotid duplex. Echo.

01:01.750 --> 01:03.460
CT to rule out stroke,

01:03.460 --> 01:05.500
tremors,
intracranial hemorrhage.

01:05.500 --> 01:07.620
Urinalysis
to rule out UTI.

01:07.620 --> 01:09.170
Did they run
a tox screen?

01:09.170 --> 01:12.120
Uh, and you
ran a tox screen?

01:12.120 --> 01:13.210
Clean.

01:13.210 --> 01:15.380
Okay.
Well, thank you.

01:15.380 --> 01:17.670
Uh, we'll confirm
when we've received them.

01:17.670 --> 01:20.710
[ Sighs ]
Let's round up the troops.

01:22.540 --> 01:24.540
We all have moments
we'd rather not relive.

01:24.540 --> 01:27.580
♪ My father's guarding me ♪

01:27.580 --> 01:29.380
Hey, I just checked
on the kids upstairs.

01:29.380 --> 01:30.750
Is he here yet?

01:30.750 --> 01:31.830
En route.

01:31.830 --> 01:34.000
And I volunteered to
take over Pierce's cases

01:34.000 --> 01:35.540
so that she can
focus on Richard.

01:35.540 --> 01:37.920
And I'm still catching up
after the conference,

01:37.920 --> 01:40.880
so I'm supposed to be
in three places now at once.

01:40.880 --> 01:43.380
You know, I'm gonna
rearrange the cake thing

01:43.380 --> 01:44.960
and see if my mom can
take care of the kids tonight.

01:44.960 --> 01:46.170
You need some sleep.

01:46.170 --> 01:47.710
Cake thing?
What cake thing?

01:47.710 --> 01:49.290
You asked for
the wedding planner

01:49.290 --> 01:51.250
to bring over a bunch of cakes
for us to try?

01:51.250 --> 01:53.380
Oh, right. God, I-I'm sorry.
I -- It's just --

01:53.380 --> 01:55.250
No, no, no. No.
I get it. We all are.

01:55.250 --> 01:57.250
Yeah. It's Richard.

01:58.460 --> 01:59.380
See ya.

02:01.750 --> 02:03.580
You think your body's
reached maximum capacity,

02:03.580 --> 02:05.620
and then you just
keep growing.

02:05.620 --> 02:07.380
I'm a human tissue
expander.

02:07.380 --> 02:08.790
No. You're --

02:08.790 --> 02:10.380
If you say glowing,
we're done.

02:11.750 --> 02:13.460
Any updates on Richard?

02:13.460 --> 02:14.880
No.

02:14.880 --> 02:16.710
But I've cleared my day
to work him up.

02:16.710 --> 02:17.790
Ow!

02:17.790 --> 02:19.330
Oh. What happened?

02:19.330 --> 02:21.420
You okay? Is the baby okay?
Should I page OB?

02:21.420 --> 02:23.330
No, I'm fine.
It was just a big kick.

02:23.330 --> 02:25.080
We still have
a couple weeks left.

02:25.080 --> 02:26.750
You can't have a panic attack
every time the baby kicks.

02:26.750 --> 02:28.620
[ Chuckles ]
Can't make any promises.

02:30.120 --> 02:31.670
[ Laughter ]

02:31.670 --> 02:33.540
Your mom made these
for you every day?

02:33.540 --> 02:34.790
Why did you move out?

02:34.790 --> 02:36.460
She also folded
my underwear,

02:36.460 --> 02:38.290
threw away articles
of clothing

02:38.290 --> 02:40.000
that didn't flatter
my nice butt,

02:40.000 --> 02:41.620
and every time I tried
to talk about a problem,

02:41.620 --> 02:44.920
she just shoved
a plate of food at me.

02:44.920 --> 02:46.750
Like I said,
I don't get it.

02:46.750 --> 02:48.040
Well, I can't go back.

02:49.290 --> 02:52.040
You replaced me with
Schmitt, didn't you?

02:53.250 --> 02:54.290
He's gonna be your
new best friend,

02:54.290 --> 02:56.000
and I'm gonna be with
my kid all the time,

02:56.000 --> 02:58.380
covered in bodily fluids.

02:58.380 --> 03:00.620
Sorry. Just, um...
[ Clears throat ]

03:00.620 --> 03:02.580
due date's
getting closer.

03:02.580 --> 03:03.790
I'm starting to, uh,

03:03.790 --> 03:06.120
wrap my head around the fact
that my life's over.

03:06.120 --> 03:08.210
Well...
you had a good run.

03:11.540 --> 03:14.080
Yeah. I did.

03:14.080 --> 03:17.380
We've got a 65-year-old male

03:17.380 --> 03:20.540
suffering from
memory lapses, tremors,

03:20.540 --> 03:24.250
depression and mood swings,
and erratic behavior.

03:24.250 --> 03:26.500
Yes, I am talking about
Richard Webber,

03:26.500 --> 03:28.330
but today, he is not
the Richard Webber

03:28.330 --> 03:29.500
you know and love.

03:29.500 --> 03:31.580
He is our number-one patient.

03:31.580 --> 03:35.380
Two days ago,
he suffered a public...

03:35.380 --> 03:37.170
episode at
a medical conference.

03:37.170 --> 03:39.750
Patient's history includes
an appendectomy,

03:39.750 --> 03:42.170
a hip replacement,
surgery for a brain tumor

03:42.170 --> 03:44.040
pressing on his optic nerve.

03:44.040 --> 03:46.500
He was also electrocuted
several years ago,

03:46.500 --> 03:50.080
which led to surgery for
a pancreatic pseudocyst.

03:50.080 --> 03:52.620
Jo did that surgery
for the pseudocyst.

03:52.620 --> 03:54.290
Oh, sorry. Uh, Dr. Jo.
Let's review what
we have so far.

03:54.290 --> 03:56.460
You're crashing with
an attending. We get it.

03:56.460 --> 03:59.250
This is a list
of possible diagnoses.

03:59.250 --> 04:01.330
Some, we have
already ruled out.

04:01.330 --> 04:03.040
This, we still need to.

04:03.040 --> 04:04.210
Meredith.

04:04.210 --> 04:05.620
Uh, we'll run
all the labs.

04:05.620 --> 04:07.920
We'll do the blood cultures,
vitamin levels,

04:07.920 --> 04:09.920
check the thyroid function,

04:09.920 --> 04:11.420
and we'll check the urine
for heavy metals.

04:11.420 --> 04:13.120
Mm-hmm.
Prepare yourselves.

04:13.120 --> 04:14.580
He's not himself.

04:14.580 --> 04:15.540
We saw the video.

04:18.040 --> 04:19.830
Bailey: Unless you get called
in for something emergent,

04:19.830 --> 04:21.420
this is your job today.

04:21.420 --> 04:22.330
Yes?

04:22.330 --> 04:23.830
Uh...hi, Dr. Bailey.

04:23.830 --> 04:24.920
Hi. Tom Koracick, neuro.

04:24.920 --> 04:26.210
I know we don't
want to think it,

04:26.210 --> 04:28.330
but have we ruled out,
uh, dementia?

04:30.210 --> 04:31.580
Maggie:
No, we have not.

04:31.580 --> 04:33.830
Get a PET scan,
throw in a beta-amyloid tracer,

04:33.830 --> 04:34.880
and look for Alzheimer's.

04:34.880 --> 04:36.710
It's not Alzheimer's.

04:36.710 --> 04:39.420
Everything is on the table.
Nothing is out of the question.

04:39.420 --> 04:41.040
Let's get to work.

04:41.040 --> 04:46.620
♪♪

04:46.620 --> 04:49.750
Here he is. Dr. Lincoln,
meet Vera and Herschel Katano.

04:49.750 --> 04:52.710
I just did her ER intake,
and we got imaging back.

04:52.710 --> 04:54.620
Lisfranc injury with,

04:54.620 --> 04:56.460
uh, fractured first
and second metatarsals.

04:56.460 --> 04:58.330
Link: Oh, nasty break.
What happened?

04:58.330 --> 05:01.040
Uh, we were
in our home office,

05:01.040 --> 05:03.000
and I was standing
on a chair

05:03.000 --> 05:06.290
reaching for this textbook,
"The Elements of Statistics."

05:06.290 --> 05:08.380
We're professors at U-Dub.
Mm-hmm.

05:08.380 --> 05:10.170
It has one
particularly useful section

05:10.170 --> 05:11.710
on game theory
that I love.

05:11.710 --> 05:14.120
The contents of the text
are irrelevant, dear.

05:14.120 --> 05:15.250
Oh, right.

05:15.250 --> 05:17.290
Well,
it's a hefty tome.

05:17.290 --> 05:19.080
And as I was
pulling it out,

05:19.080 --> 05:21.040
it slipped and landed
on my wife's foot.

05:21.040 --> 05:22.380
It's really broken?

05:22.380 --> 05:24.380
It's really broken,
but we'll fix it,

05:24.380 --> 05:25.880
and we'll put her toes
back in place.

05:25.880 --> 05:27.170
[ Chuckles ]

05:27.170 --> 05:29.830
A book lands exactly
wrong on her foot.

05:29.830 --> 05:31.170
What are the chances?

05:31.170 --> 05:33.790
Uh, certainly higher than
getting struck by lightning,

05:33.790 --> 05:35.290
but less than getting
in a car accident.

05:35.290 --> 05:37.120
What are the chances
of you letting

05:37.120 --> 05:39.250
these nice doctors
do their job, hmm?

05:39.250 --> 05:40.830
Hunt, you give me
a hand in the OR?

05:40.830 --> 05:42.040
Yep. I'll see you
up there.

05:42.040 --> 05:43.920
I'm supposed to make
a presentation of a paper

05:43.920 --> 05:45.710
in a university
in two days.

05:45.710 --> 05:47.750
You still can.
From the chair.

05:47.750 --> 05:49.330
[ Chuckles ]

05:49.330 --> 05:50.880
Can you stomp
on his foot, hmm?

05:50.880 --> 05:52.290
[ Chuckles ]

05:52.290 --> 05:54.000
[ Sighs ]

05:54.000 --> 05:56.460
Look, I can
get myself into a bed.

05:58.710 --> 06:00.170
[ Sighs ]

06:01.580 --> 06:03.250
Sorry. Hey.

06:03.250 --> 06:05.330
Where have you been? And what
the hell are you wearing?

06:05.330 --> 06:07.330
I was with Warren on the
physician response team vehicle.

06:07.330 --> 06:09.330
Don't worry about it.
You smell like
a garbage fire.

06:09.330 --> 06:10.420
Okay. Richard,
how are you feeling?

06:10.420 --> 06:11.830
How am I feeling?

06:11.830 --> 06:14.210
Well, I was just wheeled
into my own damn hospital

06:14.210 --> 06:16.670
like I was someone who's
lost control of their faculties.

06:16.670 --> 06:18.960
[ Sighs ]
We're gonna run a few more
tests, okay?

06:18.960 --> 06:20.120
No, that is not okay.

06:20.120 --> 06:22.750
And stop treating me
like I'm an infant.

06:22.750 --> 06:24.670
Catherine was with me
at the conference.

06:24.670 --> 06:26.880
Will you tell them that
they're being ridiculous?

06:26.880 --> 06:28.040
Actually, Catherine --

06:28.040 --> 06:29.710
Yes, sweetheart,
I was there,

06:29.710 --> 06:31.460
and your speech
was brilliant!

06:31.460 --> 06:33.540
But you started feeling
badly right after.

06:33.540 --> 06:35.830
So, please, let us just
take a few more tests,

06:35.830 --> 06:37.460
and then we can go home.

06:37.460 --> 06:38.420
Promise.

06:40.540 --> 06:42.420
Oh, alright.

06:42.420 --> 06:43.750
But I'm only doing
this for Cleopatra.

06:43.750 --> 06:45.040
[ Laughs ]

06:45.040 --> 06:49.710
♪♪

06:49.710 --> 06:52.040
Add visual
and auditory hallucinations

06:52.040 --> 06:53.330
to the list
of symptoms.

06:53.330 --> 06:54.380
Okay.

06:58.920 --> 07:01.790
Hey.
Tom, I wanted to...

07:01.790 --> 07:03.580
Not get married
to someone else?

07:03.580 --> 07:05.040
I wanted to talk.

07:05.040 --> 07:07.290
No, I got it, but sincerely,
there's nothing to talk about.

07:07.290 --> 07:08.710
I hope you
and Strawberry Shortcake

07:08.710 --> 07:10.750
live happily ever af--

07:10.750 --> 07:12.620
Tom, what is it?

07:12.620 --> 07:16.540
♪♪

07:16.540 --> 07:17.830
Tom.

07:17.830 --> 07:19.540
It's been a long time.

07:23.420 --> 07:25.620
Hi. I'm --
I'm Dr. Teddy Altman.

07:25.620 --> 07:27.710
Hi.
I'm, uh, Dana Hamilton,

07:27.710 --> 07:28.790
formerly Koracick.

07:30.120 --> 07:32.380
And this is my son,
Guthrie.

07:32.380 --> 07:35.420
Honey, say hi to
Dr. Altman and Dr. Tom.

07:35.420 --> 07:36.580
Guthrie:
Nice to meet you.

07:36.580 --> 07:38.420
My mom said you might be
kind of freaked out

07:38.420 --> 07:40.540
because I look like my brother
who died before I was born.

07:42.120 --> 07:44.120
[ Chuckles ]
And I would say sorry,
but I can't really

07:44.120 --> 07:45.580
change my face, so...

07:46.790 --> 07:49.210
[ Clears throat ]
God, you even sound
a little bit like him.

07:49.210 --> 07:51.210
Maybe you -- Can you
change your voice?

07:51.210 --> 07:52.500
[ Chuckles nervously ]

07:52.500 --> 07:53.540
[ High-pitched ]
I can try.

07:53.540 --> 07:55.000
[ Laughs ]

07:57.330 --> 08:00.750
I know the resemblance
to David is uncanny.

08:00.750 --> 08:02.580
I'm sorry.
I should have called.

08:02.580 --> 08:04.330
But I didn't even know
that you would pick up

08:04.330 --> 08:06.040
if you saw that
it was me.

08:07.250 --> 08:08.330
Um...

08:08.330 --> 08:10.670
Guthrie has
a brain tumor.

08:10.670 --> 08:13.080
And apparently,
it's spread to his spine.

08:13.080 --> 08:15.540
And it's bad, Tom.

08:17.540 --> 08:19.000
I wouldn't have come
if it weren't.

08:19.000 --> 08:20.880
I just wouldn't have come.

08:20.880 --> 08:22.750
Yeah.

08:22.750 --> 08:24.210
You know what,
let's get you checked in,

08:24.210 --> 08:25.120
and then we'll take it
from there.

08:25.120 --> 08:26.120
Tom,
do you want me to...?

08:26.120 --> 08:27.460
Mm-hmm.
Yeah.

08:27.460 --> 08:30.290
Mrs. Hamilton, will you
follow me, please?

08:30.290 --> 08:32.540
[ High-pitched ]
Nice to meet you, Dr. Tom.

08:32.540 --> 08:36.920
♪♪

08:48.750 --> 08:51.040
Guthrie Hamilton,
10 years old,

08:51.040 --> 08:52.710
diagnosed with primary
medulloblastoma in his brain

08:52.710 --> 08:55.080
that has spread to
his spine at C3.

08:55.080 --> 08:56.750
Presents with
sensory deficits

08:56.750 --> 08:58.750
and motor weakness
in his extremities.

08:58.750 --> 09:02.540
He was in his cooking class,
and he just collapsed.

09:02.540 --> 09:04.500
It was awful.

09:04.500 --> 09:06.170
Guthrie:
Pastry class, actually.

09:07.210 --> 09:08.750
We were baking
croissants.

09:08.750 --> 09:10.330
I never got to try mine,

09:10.330 --> 09:11.960
but the teacher said
they were pretty good.

09:11.960 --> 09:13.790
If you were stranded
on a desert island

09:13.790 --> 09:16.000
and you could only have
one food, what would it be?

09:16.000 --> 09:17.750
He asks everyone this.

09:17.750 --> 09:18.750
Hummus.

09:18.750 --> 09:19.500
No.

09:19.500 --> 09:20.880
Brie.

09:22.170 --> 09:23.500
What about you,
Dr. Tom?

09:24.920 --> 09:27.330
Um...

09:27.330 --> 09:28.750
escargot.

09:28.750 --> 09:30.040
A man of excellent taste.

09:30.040 --> 09:31.540
[ Chuckles ]
Um...
[ Clears throat ]

09:31.540 --> 09:34.710
we should, uh -- We should
get him some new scans.

09:34.710 --> 09:37.500
Let's -- Let's -- Let's get him
up there right away.

09:37.500 --> 09:38.460
Excuse me.

09:42.120 --> 09:43.460
I already
paged Shepherd.

09:43.460 --> 09:45.290
I don't know what
your ex-wife was thinking.

09:45.290 --> 09:46.500
She was thinking
I'm the best.

09:46.500 --> 09:48.670
She was thinking
I could never let this child die

09:48.670 --> 09:50.580
if there's a single thing
I could do to stop it.

09:51.960 --> 09:53.830
It's David, Teddy.

09:53.830 --> 09:56.580
It's him. And it's not.
And I'm...

09:56.580 --> 09:57.750
[ Chuckles ]

09:57.750 --> 10:01.210
Tom, I'm here.
I'm staying close.

10:02.420 --> 10:03.460
[ Sighs ]

10:05.960 --> 10:07.580
Can you walk?
[ Clears throat ] Yeah.

10:07.580 --> 10:08.750
Okay.

10:08.750 --> 10:10.460
Yeah.

10:10.460 --> 10:14.790
♪♪

10:14.790 --> 10:16.210
[ Exhales shakily ]

10:19.670 --> 10:22.790
I'm late? Felt like
I was walking fast.

10:22.790 --> 10:27.330
Abdominal midline incision
extending from the xiphoid

10:27.330 --> 10:29.290
to just under the umbilicus.

10:29.290 --> 10:30.540
What's that about?

10:30.540 --> 10:32.290
Uh, he's going through
the steps of a Whipple

10:32.290 --> 10:33.920
to prove to us that
he has not lost his mind.

10:35.330 --> 10:38.120
"Famous Surgeon Implodes
at Medical Conference."

10:38.120 --> 10:39.750
"Medical Meltdown
of the Year."

10:39.750 --> 10:41.080
It doesn't stop.

10:42.540 --> 10:44.620
Catherine's on the phone with
the foundation publicist

10:44.620 --> 10:46.290
to try to scrub it off
of the Internet,

10:46.290 --> 10:47.670
which isn't really
possible.

10:47.670 --> 10:49.830
Inspect the peritoneum
and the surface

10:49.830 --> 10:51.380
of the liver
for metastasis.

10:51.380 --> 10:53.170
"When you think
you cured cancer

10:53.170 --> 10:54.540
but you really
just got dumped."

10:56.500 --> 10:58.170
[ Scoffs ]
I hate everyone.

10:58.170 --> 11:00.170
I -- Myself included.

11:00.170 --> 11:02.000
I was so busy
sexing it up with Winston

11:02.000 --> 11:04.170
I didn't even realize
what was happening.

11:04.170 --> 11:05.540
And I should have.

11:05.540 --> 11:07.170
He called me Meredith
when he saw me.

11:08.620 --> 11:10.170
Wait, what's a Winston?

11:10.170 --> 11:11.500
I'll tell you later.

11:11.500 --> 11:13.960
Hepatic flexure
of the right colon

11:13.960 --> 11:18.210
mobilized and reflected
medially.

11:18.210 --> 11:19.880
There.

11:19.880 --> 11:23.210
Now, would I be able to tell
you all that if I lost my mind?

11:23.210 --> 11:25.040
The answer is
no, I wouldn't.

11:25.040 --> 11:26.790
Is he right?
About the steps?

11:26.790 --> 11:28.380
He is right.

11:28.380 --> 11:30.000
You're doing great, Richard.
You're almost there.

11:31.380 --> 11:32.670
[ Monitor beeps ]

11:32.670 --> 11:35.120
[ Sighs ]

11:35.120 --> 11:37.120
Okay.

11:37.120 --> 11:40.670
No indication of Lewy body
dementia or Pick's disease.

11:40.670 --> 11:42.920
No increased signal
to the temporoparietal lobes,

11:42.920 --> 11:44.830
so maybe not Alzheimer's.

11:44.830 --> 11:46.670
But if it was in
the early stages,
we wouldn't see it.

11:46.670 --> 11:48.250
It isn't Alzheimer's.

11:48.250 --> 11:50.170
I've had a front-row seat
to this disease.

11:50.170 --> 11:52.250
This is not it.

11:52.250 --> 11:59.380
♪♪

11:59.380 --> 12:01.080
Are we done yet?

12:02.080 --> 12:03.790
Link:
Drilling the K-wire.

12:03.790 --> 12:05.880
[ Drill whirring ]
Any word on Webber?

12:05.880 --> 12:09.210
Last I heard,
just more tests.

12:09.210 --> 12:12.500
Amelia was up all night
watching that conference video

12:12.500 --> 12:15.000
over and over again,
looking for clues.

12:15.000 --> 12:16.250
Worried me.

12:16.250 --> 12:17.620
Yeah. They've always
been close.

12:17.620 --> 12:19.210
I know, but stress
and exhaustion

12:19.210 --> 12:21.250
can cause hormone levels
to fluctuate,

12:21.250 --> 12:24.040
which can induce
preterm labor,

12:24.040 --> 12:25.830
and, you know, suddenly,
we've got a little dude

12:25.830 --> 12:27.580
who showed up to the party
too early.
[ Drill whirring ]

12:27.580 --> 12:29.750
Well, Amelia's close
to term, you know?

12:29.750 --> 12:31.040
Baby's gonna be just fine.

12:32.710 --> 12:33.790
You're nervous?

12:33.790 --> 12:35.540
Name a worry,
I've had it.

12:35.540 --> 12:37.460
Will Amelia have
an easy delivery?

12:37.460 --> 12:39.620
Will we make it to
the hospital on time?

12:39.620 --> 12:41.170
Will the baby
be scared of me?

12:41.170 --> 12:42.330
[ Chuckles ]
Scared of you?

12:42.330 --> 12:43.670
Yeah, I mean,
I've got big hands.

12:43.670 --> 12:45.540
I don't know. What if
that freaks the baby out?

12:45.540 --> 12:48.540
I know what you're gonna say --
that I'm just spinning out

12:48.540 --> 12:50.540
and soon as the baby
gets here, I'll be fine.

12:50.540 --> 12:52.290
Nope. I wasn't
gonna say that.

12:52.290 --> 12:53.750
You weren't?
No, because I like you.

12:53.750 --> 12:56.170
So while everyone else
is saying "Cherish this time,"

12:56.170 --> 12:57.830
I'm gonna tell you
the truth, okay?

12:57.830 --> 12:59.460
Parenthood
is scary as hell.

12:59.460 --> 13:01.790
Your kid is in the safest place
he's ever gonna be right now.

13:01.790 --> 13:04.210
When he comes out,
you're never gonna sleep again.

13:04.210 --> 13:05.420
Wire cutters.

13:05.420 --> 13:06.250
Thanks.

13:06.250 --> 13:07.250
[ Whistling ]

13:07.250 --> 13:09.750
[ Indistinct talking ]

13:09.750 --> 13:11.330
[ Siren wailing in distance ]

13:11.330 --> 13:12.500
Hey.
Hey, what's up?

13:12.500 --> 13:14.420
Oh, we're swamped.
I need you to jump in.

13:14.420 --> 13:16.120
I need you to evaluate
beds 2 through 7

13:16.120 --> 13:17.540
for smoke inhalation
and clear them.

13:17.540 --> 13:19.000
But I've been helping
with Dr. Webber.

13:19.000 --> 13:20.880
Hey, Schmitt, no offense,
but whatever's wrong with Webber

13:20.880 --> 13:21.880
won't be solved
by a resident.

13:21.880 --> 13:24.540
Oh. Uh, okay.

13:24.540 --> 13:26.210
Why are you still
standing here?!

13:26.210 --> 13:27.670
Alright. I'm going.
I'm going.

13:27.670 --> 13:28.500
Sorry.

13:28.500 --> 13:30.620
Take him over
to bed 10.

13:30.620 --> 13:32.920
So, I-I-I'm sitting on this
park bench the other day, right,

13:32.920 --> 13:35.080
and I look across,
and I see this squirrel,

13:35.080 --> 13:38.670
and he's -- he's hauling this
giant slice of pizza, right?

13:38.670 --> 13:40.330
[ Laughs ]
Then he starts
dragging it up the street.

13:40.330 --> 13:42.000
I mean, the thing must have
been twice his size.

13:42.000 --> 13:43.830
I don't even know how
he was doing it.
[ Laughs ]

13:43.830 --> 13:45.040
[ Bailey clears throat ]

13:45.040 --> 13:47.580
Oh. You finally here
to let me go?

13:47.580 --> 13:49.920
Um...waiting
on blood cultures.

13:49.920 --> 13:52.580
T-The ER's slammed,
so the lab's backed up.

13:52.580 --> 13:53.670
Dr. DeLuca?

13:53.670 --> 13:56.000
[ Indistinct talking on P.A. ]

13:59.330 --> 14:01.620
Have I been
in any way unclear

14:01.620 --> 14:03.170
about your suspension?
[ Sighs ]

14:03.170 --> 14:05.170
Come on, Bailey.
I can't visit a friend?

14:05.170 --> 14:07.250
Webber's a mentor of mine.
We hang out socially.

14:07.250 --> 14:08.960
I saw the news.
I got worried.

14:08.960 --> 14:11.420
Fine. But after visiting hours,
you're gone.

14:11.420 --> 14:12.670
Understood.

14:12.670 --> 14:14.290
Hey, y-you need to add
decreased appetite

14:14.290 --> 14:15.500
to his list of symptoms.

14:15.500 --> 14:17.620
DeLuca!
Look, Dr. Riley says

14:17.620 --> 14:19.620
that we learn more from
our patients in conversation

14:19.620 --> 14:21.250
than traditional questioning,
right?

14:21.250 --> 14:23.120
So, she's out of the country
right now, but she e-mailed me

14:23.120 --> 14:25.040
this list of topics
to get him talking,

14:25.040 --> 14:26.420
a-a-and I think
that it could open more avenues

14:26.420 --> 14:27.880
for -- for research,
and -- and he could --

14:27.880 --> 14:29.170
Visiting hours
are almost over.

14:30.380 --> 14:31.830
And forward me that list.

14:31.830 --> 14:33.210
[ Chuckles ]

14:34.540 --> 14:35.830
Okay.

14:35.830 --> 14:37.960
[ Indistinct talking on P.A. ]

14:37.960 --> 14:39.920
Hey. You paged me?

14:39.920 --> 14:41.880
I'm still pretty busy with
the Richard thing, so...

14:41.880 --> 14:44.080
We have a 10-year-old
with a medulloblastoma

14:44.080 --> 14:46.040
and a drop met
on his cervical spine.

14:46.040 --> 14:48.420
And...Koracick needs me
because...?

14:48.420 --> 14:49.830
It's his ex-wife's son.

14:49.830 --> 14:52.290
Apparently, the kid looks
exactly like David.

14:52.290 --> 14:53.420
David was --

14:53.420 --> 14:55.210
No, I know.
I-I knew David.

14:55.210 --> 14:56.790
Oh, my God.

14:56.790 --> 14:58.830
What are the chances Dana's
gonna lose another 10-year-old?

14:58.830 --> 15:00.250
Hopefully not.

15:00.250 --> 15:02.040
Hopefully
you can save him.

15:03.330 --> 15:05.290
[ Whispering ]
'Cause Tom certainly can't.

15:06.580 --> 15:08.290
[ Clears throat ]
The tumor is getting bigger.

15:08.290 --> 15:10.120
It's encroaching
on the brain stem.

15:11.960 --> 15:13.170
Do they know?

15:14.620 --> 15:15.750
I'll talk to them.

15:15.750 --> 15:17.420
I will take it from here.

15:17.420 --> 15:18.460
Okay.

15:23.920 --> 15:26.710
Dr. Lincoln was able to reduce
the toes back into their place.

15:26.710 --> 15:28.620
The surgery went
extremely well.

15:28.620 --> 15:30.170
Link: We'll leave
the splint on,

15:30.170 --> 15:31.790
but no weight-bearing
on this foot for 12 weeks.

15:31.790 --> 15:33.170
You understand?

15:33.170 --> 15:36.960
Oh, thank you
so much, doctors.

15:36.960 --> 15:38.540
Thank -- Thank you.
Sure.

15:38.540 --> 15:39.790
Hear that, Vera?

15:39.790 --> 15:41.500
I'm waiting on you
for 12 weeks.

15:41.500 --> 15:43.380
84 days.

15:43.380 --> 15:45.330
Hand and...foot, honey.
[ Chuckles ]

15:45.330 --> 15:46.460
Cup of tea,

15:46.460 --> 15:48.580
those samosas from
the place you love.

15:48.580 --> 15:50.460
[ Chuckles ]
Ha! Whatever you need.

15:50.460 --> 15:52.540
We'll check on you in
a couple hours, okay?

15:52.540 --> 15:55.120
♪ Excuse me, but why
are all of you singing? ♪

15:58.420 --> 16:00.670
♪ Weren't all of you
singing just now? ♪

16:00.670 --> 16:03.000
Uh, s-s-sweetie, uh...

16:03.000 --> 16:05.960
no one's singing,
besides you.

16:05.960 --> 16:08.040
♪ What is happening? ♪

16:08.040 --> 16:10.420
Maybe we should --
Yep. Paging neuro.

16:10.420 --> 16:11.500
♪ Oh! ♪

16:18.000 --> 16:19.960
[ Indistinct talking on P.A. ]

16:19.960 --> 16:26.290
♪♪

16:26.290 --> 16:32.750
♪♪

16:32.750 --> 16:34.210
You need to work harder.

16:36.170 --> 16:38.540
Everyone's doing the best
that they can, Mom.

16:38.540 --> 16:41.670
Well, you look like
a bunch of feckless interns.

16:41.670 --> 16:43.790
Figure this out.

16:43.790 --> 16:50.380
♪♪

16:50.380 --> 16:51.960
It's happening again.

16:51.960 --> 16:53.880
I'm gonna lose him,
too.

16:53.880 --> 16:55.290
I promise I will try
to get the brain tumor

16:55.290 --> 16:57.420
and the spinal met
in one surgery.

16:57.420 --> 17:00.000
You are in great hands
with Dr. Shepherd.

17:00.000 --> 17:02.620
No offense,
but we came here f-for Tom.

17:02.620 --> 17:04.170
[ Scoffs ]

17:05.620 --> 17:08.830
Dana, I use all the same
techniques as Tom.

17:08.830 --> 17:10.170
I trained under him.

17:10.170 --> 17:12.750
He taught me
everything he knows.

17:12.750 --> 17:14.540
[ Exhales shakily ]

17:16.290 --> 17:18.960
I did not bring him
here to hurt you.

17:18.960 --> 17:20.750
I-I ran out of ideas.

17:20.750 --> 17:23.710
I didn't know
what else to do.

17:23.710 --> 17:25.540
I can't...

17:25.540 --> 17:27.960
I can't, Tom.

17:27.960 --> 17:29.540
Tom, I can't
go through this again.

17:29.540 --> 17:31.250
I won't survive.

17:31.250 --> 17:32.750
I won't survive.

17:35.000 --> 17:36.420
I can't.

17:36.420 --> 17:38.750
Uh, we're family.
Or were.

17:38.750 --> 17:41.790
And h-- hospital policy,
uh, forbids surgeons

17:41.790 --> 17:43.120
from operating on --

17:43.120 --> 17:44.960
And my schedule is
extremely hectic.

17:44.960 --> 17:46.080
I'm being
paged right now.

17:46.080 --> 17:48.290
Shepherd is --
she's excellent.

17:50.790 --> 17:52.120
I've got Guthrie.
Why don't you stay with him?

17:52.120 --> 17:53.040
Excuse me.

17:55.250 --> 17:56.710
[ Humming ]

17:56.710 --> 17:58.790
Did you give her some weird kind
of pain meds or something?

17:58.790 --> 18:00.250
Is she loopy?

18:00.250 --> 18:02.460
♪ Herschel's voice
goes up an octave higher ♪

18:02.460 --> 18:04.290
♪ When he's anxious ♪

18:04.290 --> 18:06.790
[ Humming ]
She had a general anesthesia
and a post-op painkiller,

18:06.790 --> 18:09.210
but we don't usually see
singing as a side effect.

18:09.210 --> 18:10.670
Pupils are equal
and reactive.

18:10.670 --> 18:11.750
Usually?

18:11.750 --> 18:13.500
Or...not ever.

18:13.500 --> 18:15.540
Vera:
♪ I feel completely present ♪

18:15.540 --> 18:18.500
♪ I just hear all
this music in my head ♪

18:18.500 --> 18:20.380
♪ It is remarkable ♪

18:20.380 --> 18:22.080
Tom Koracick, neuro.

18:22.080 --> 18:24.460
These doctors
broke my wife.

18:24.460 --> 18:26.960
Vera had surgery on her
Lisfranc injury this morning.

18:26.960 --> 18:29.580
She woke up alert
but...singing.

18:29.580 --> 18:31.290
[ Humming ]
Physical exam's normal.
Labs normal.

18:31.290 --> 18:33.580
Everything appears...
normal.

18:33.580 --> 18:35.710
Koracick: Uh, let's order
a brain MRI and an EEG.

18:35.710 --> 18:38.250
Vera, we're gonna rule out
an intra-operative stroke,

18:38.250 --> 18:40.540
but this could be something
called "musicophilia."

18:40.540 --> 18:42.040
What on Earth is that?

18:42.040 --> 18:44.920
A spectrum of neurological
phenomena related to music.

18:44.920 --> 18:47.120
So, you've seen
this before?

18:47.120 --> 18:48.620
No. It's
exceedingly rare.

18:48.620 --> 18:50.170
How do you fix it?

18:50.170 --> 18:51.920
You --
Singing lessons.

18:51.920 --> 18:53.960
Page me when she's
in the scanner.

18:53.960 --> 18:56.250
♪ Herschel ♪

18:56.250 --> 18:59.880
♪ I wish you could be
experiencing this ♪

18:59.880 --> 19:01.580
I-I am, dear.

19:01.580 --> 19:03.120
I am.

19:03.120 --> 19:04.750
[ Humming ]

19:04.750 --> 19:08.830
[ Indistinct talking on P.A. ]

19:08.830 --> 19:11.330
Nico just posted again
on Instagram.

19:11.330 --> 19:12.620
He's having
the time of his life.

19:12.620 --> 19:13.960
His smile doesn't
even look fake.

19:13.960 --> 19:15.920
It's like
I never existed!

19:15.920 --> 19:18.040
Are you really talking
to me about this while
we're in gridlock?

19:18.040 --> 19:19.960
Well, I just assessed
beds 3 and 4.

19:19.960 --> 19:21.920
Congratulations.
We're still gridlocked.

19:21.920 --> 19:22.960
Is that my fault?

19:22.960 --> 19:24.960
It's not not your fault!

19:24.960 --> 19:26.920
Schmitt,
half the attendings

19:26.920 --> 19:28.500
are in a room right now
working on Webber.

19:28.500 --> 19:31.500
This is your moment
to step up, to rise, to shine,

19:31.500 --> 19:34.670
to take care of
incoming before you get
run over by a gurney!

19:34.670 --> 19:36.380
And if you look
at your phone one more time,

19:36.380 --> 19:38.580
I'll give you so much scut,
you'll wish you were never born!

19:38.580 --> 19:40.040
[ Sighs ]

19:40.040 --> 19:42.170
[ Humming ]

19:45.250 --> 19:47.710
Hey. So, Shepherd is
taking Guthrie to pre-op.

19:47.710 --> 19:49.210
Thank you.

19:49.210 --> 19:52.080
[ Humming continues ]

19:52.080 --> 19:54.120
[ Click, humming stops ]

19:56.460 --> 19:57.710
[ Sighs ]

19:57.710 --> 20:01.540
God, ever since David died,
I've had this thought --

20:01.540 --> 20:06.250
What if I got to the hospital
in time to operate?

20:06.250 --> 20:10.040
Maybe...I could
have saved him.

20:10.040 --> 20:13.620
And now it's like...

20:13.620 --> 20:17.040
he's here, and I can't --
I can't be in the same room

20:17.040 --> 20:19.620
without feeling like
I'm...drowning.

20:21.380 --> 20:24.170
That thought I've been
holding on to -- it's a lie.

20:26.620 --> 20:28.580
[ Clears throat ]

20:28.580 --> 20:30.290
I got to update
my patient.

20:34.380 --> 20:37.540
Okay, so,
the first one is,

20:37.540 --> 20:40.830
we are going to repeat
this pattern.

20:42.540 --> 20:44.580
Mm...

20:46.500 --> 20:49.580
Um...you know what?
Let's come back to that one.

20:49.580 --> 20:50.710
Okay, sure.

20:50.710 --> 20:53.670
So, let's draw
this 3-D cube.

21:02.290 --> 21:03.790
Mm-hmm.

21:05.540 --> 21:07.830
Okay...

21:10.000 --> 21:11.620
Okay.

21:11.620 --> 21:13.540
Right here.

21:13.540 --> 21:16.000
Well, why don't we just,
uh, skip to this one here

21:16.000 --> 21:18.380
and draw a clock?

21:18.380 --> 21:21.290
And we want the time
to say 10 past 11:00.

21:21.290 --> 21:22.420
Okay.

21:22.420 --> 21:25.540
Alright, this is --
Okay. I got this.

21:25.540 --> 21:27.250
Yeah.
You got this, Richard.

21:27.250 --> 21:28.880
[ Grunts ]
Yeah.

21:30.210 --> 21:32.210
Uh-huh.

21:32.210 --> 21:33.250
Great.

21:33.250 --> 21:35.620
Mm-hmm.

21:35.620 --> 21:37.620
[ Clears throat ]

21:37.620 --> 21:46.580
♪♪

21:46.580 --> 21:48.120
Okay, you know, we can take
a break for right now.

21:48.120 --> 21:49.460
We can
come back to this.

21:49.460 --> 21:51.080
Okay, well, hang on.
I wasn't finished with it.

21:51.080 --> 21:52.500
It's okay.

21:52.500 --> 21:54.880
I'm sure you're tired,
and it's been a lot.

21:54.880 --> 21:58.500
♪♪

22:04.120 --> 22:06.000
Vera: [ Humming ]

22:06.000 --> 22:07.710
♪ I guess singing
could help hold ♪

22:07.710 --> 22:10.880
♪ Students' interest
in empirical probabilities ♪

22:10.880 --> 22:13.210
Honey, you're about
to publish.

22:13.210 --> 22:14.750
We're about to publish.

22:14.750 --> 22:17.420
And you don't want people
questioning your state of mind.

22:17.420 --> 22:19.040
[ Humming ]
Koracick: There's no signs
of stroke or bleeding,

22:19.040 --> 22:20.710
and the EEG's negative
for seizures.

22:20.710 --> 22:21.880
Okay.

22:21.880 --> 22:23.960
So, she's just
like this now?

22:23.960 --> 22:25.380
Which is good news,
Herschel.

22:25.380 --> 22:26.920
It's most likely
a complication

22:26.920 --> 22:28.290
from being
under anesthesia.

22:28.290 --> 22:29.880
We're gonna keep her
here overnight

22:29.880 --> 22:31.210
for monitoring purposes,

22:31.210 --> 22:32.580
but you should be able
to take her home tomorrow.

22:32.580 --> 22:33.580
Great.

22:33.580 --> 22:34.920
Yeah. Great.

22:34.920 --> 22:37.290
[ Humming continues ]

22:37.290 --> 22:39.830
[ Sighs ]
Hey, any update on Richard?

22:39.830 --> 22:41.580
Uh, n-no idea.

22:44.290 --> 22:45.620
[ Door opens ]

22:47.830 --> 22:50.000
I'm not here
with an update.

22:50.000 --> 22:51.500
It's just me.

22:51.500 --> 22:54.080
I don't need you, Jackson.
Richard needs you.

22:54.080 --> 22:55.580
Okay, Mom...

22:55.580 --> 22:58.120
You're letting him down.
Do you know that?

22:58.120 --> 23:00.500
He's given this hospital
the best years of his life,

23:00.500 --> 23:02.420
and you all are
the best minds in the field,

23:02.420 --> 23:05.420
and no one even noticed
that he wasn't himself,

23:05.420 --> 23:07.330
that he was deteriorating?

23:07.330 --> 23:10.250
In fairness to us, I think
we thought that he was depressed

23:10.250 --> 23:11.880
because his wife
both left him

23:11.880 --> 23:14.380
and bought the hospital
that he was working at.

23:14.380 --> 23:16.830
You don't think I've been
dying inside already?

23:16.830 --> 23:18.290
I'm sure you have,
and I'm sorry, Mom,

23:18.290 --> 23:19.420
but us fighting isn't --

23:19.420 --> 23:21.250
Do you think I haven't
been kicking myself

23:21.250 --> 23:25.380
for the last 48 hours, wondering
what I would have noticed

23:25.380 --> 23:29.120
if I could just
have put aside my pride?

23:29.120 --> 23:31.170
I should have
been there.

23:31.170 --> 23:33.580
I would have
seen something.

23:33.580 --> 23:35.790
I'm his wife.

23:35.790 --> 23:37.420
I'm his wife.

23:39.290 --> 23:41.250
I'm his wife.

23:41.250 --> 23:44.500
So I can't be on his
medical team, but you can.

23:44.500 --> 23:48.500
So you get back in that war room
and figure it out.

23:50.040 --> 23:52.080
Now.

23:54.750 --> 23:56.290
[ Sniffs ] Okay.

23:59.620 --> 24:00.580
[ Sighs ]

24:02.830 --> 24:05.830
[ Door opens, closes ]

24:05.830 --> 24:09.380
♪ Is somebody bringing me
another pillow? ♪

24:09.380 --> 24:11.290
The nurses went
to get one, dear.

24:11.290 --> 24:13.500
[ Vocalizing ]
Hey. Coffee?

24:13.500 --> 24:15.040
Thanks.
Yeah.

24:15.040 --> 24:16.580
How you holding up?

24:16.580 --> 24:18.080
Mm.

24:18.080 --> 24:20.960
You know,
about five years ago,

24:20.960 --> 24:24.420
I spilled an iced tea
all over my car's dashboard.

24:24.420 --> 24:27.080
It fried something in
the electrical system

24:27.080 --> 24:29.580
and caused my seatbelt alarm
to constantly beep.

24:29.580 --> 24:31.750
Even if the belt was buckled,
"Beep, beep, beep."

24:31.750 --> 24:33.120
[ Chuckles ]

24:33.120 --> 24:35.710
I was trying to
meet a book deadline,

24:35.710 --> 24:37.500
so I couldn't
get it fixed,

24:37.500 --> 24:41.750
so for weeks --
"Beep, beep, beep."

24:41.750 --> 24:43.120
And...

24:43.120 --> 24:45.080
[ Humming ]

24:45.080 --> 24:46.460
...I learned
to live with it.

24:46.460 --> 24:49.880
It faded in the background,
almost became comforting.

24:49.880 --> 24:52.290
Will this ever fade?

24:52.290 --> 24:54.330
Maybe. Yeah.

24:54.330 --> 24:57.790
Or you could...
grow to like it?

24:57.790 --> 24:59.790
And I've read that it
can help these patients

24:59.790 --> 25:01.790
if you give them
an instrument to play.

25:01.790 --> 25:06.790
Vera and I work at home because
the library is too loud.

25:06.790 --> 25:09.380
If an oboe or something like
that comes into my life,

25:09.380 --> 25:10.880
I will have
very dark thoughts.

25:11.830 --> 25:14.250
Oh, um, please --

25:14.250 --> 25:16.750
don't tell her
that I compared her voice

25:16.750 --> 25:19.540
to the broken seatbelt
in our 1997 station wagon.

25:19.540 --> 25:20.920
[ Laughing ] No.
[ Laughs ]

25:20.920 --> 25:22.620
[ Humming stops ]

25:22.620 --> 25:24.210
It stopped.

25:24.210 --> 25:25.380
Oh, my God, it stopped.

25:25.380 --> 25:26.750
Thank you, thank you,
thank you!

25:26.750 --> 25:28.250
[ Vera wheezing,
monitor alarm beeping ]

25:28.250 --> 25:29.670
Vera! Are you okay?!

25:29.670 --> 25:31.210
What's happening?!
She's hypoxic
and tachycardic.

25:31.210 --> 25:32.620
Uh, Herschel, we need you
to wait outside.

25:32.620 --> 25:33.880
B-B-But she was fine
a second ago!

25:33.880 --> 25:36.420
I-I-I'll update you
as soon as we know anything.

25:36.420 --> 25:39.460
[ Alarm continues ]

25:39.460 --> 25:41.960
Amelia: Now we identify
the cerebellar tonsils.

25:41.960 --> 25:43.250
Taryn: That's awesome.

25:43.250 --> 25:44.580
We're not even at
the hard part yet.

25:44.580 --> 25:46.540
I still have to
resect the tumor

25:46.540 --> 25:48.500
without injuring
the brain stem.

25:48.500 --> 25:49.960
Ow!

25:49.960 --> 25:51.580
Are you okay?

25:51.580 --> 25:53.620
Yep. Great.

25:53.620 --> 25:56.210
I feel great.

25:56.210 --> 25:58.380
Okay, inspecting
the inferior vermis --

25:58.380 --> 26:01.540
Holy Mother of --
Ohh!

26:01.540 --> 26:04.710
Helm, put down the retractor
and go get Dr. Koracick.

26:04.710 --> 26:05.620
Ohh!
But, uh...

26:05.620 --> 26:08.040
Helm, I am in labor.

26:08.040 --> 26:10.290
Run!
[ Groans ]

26:10.290 --> 26:12.420
And page Atticus Lincoln!

26:12.420 --> 26:14.500
[ Groaning ]

26:20.540 --> 26:22.580
[ Moaning ]

26:22.580 --> 26:23.920
What the hell happened?

26:23.920 --> 26:25.500
I am having this
baby, like, now!

26:25.500 --> 26:27.420
Did your water break?

26:27.420 --> 26:29.170
Tom, not yet, but that
doesn't mean --
Okay, until it does,
you have time.

26:29.170 --> 26:30.960
You can finish.
Just keep going.

26:30.960 --> 26:32.540
Tom, do you hear
yourself?!

26:32.540 --> 26:33.710
I'm -- I'm -- I'm
begging you, Shepherd.

26:33.710 --> 26:35.540
Don't make me do this.

26:35.540 --> 26:37.580
Tom, you saw the scans.

26:37.580 --> 26:39.710
You and I are the best
two in this hospital,

26:39.710 --> 26:41.880
maybe this country,
to remove this tumor.

26:41.880 --> 26:44.620
This kid deserves one of us.
I can't do it.

26:44.620 --> 26:47.380
So get in there and scrub!

26:47.380 --> 26:48.170
Now!!

26:50.250 --> 26:51.830
Congratulations,
Dr. Shepherd.

26:51.830 --> 26:53.170
[ Groaning loudly ]

26:54.670 --> 26:56.460
Richard clearly has
some type

26:56.460 --> 26:58.460
of rapidly progressive
dementia,

26:58.460 --> 27:01.120
and so far, none of our tests
can point to a cause.

27:01.120 --> 27:03.920
This could
very well be --

27:03.920 --> 27:06.120
Meredith, I'm not gonna
not say it.

27:06.120 --> 27:07.830
It could --

27:07.830 --> 27:09.080
Richard?

27:10.460 --> 27:12.210
Okay, let's split up.

27:12.210 --> 27:13.620
Uh, I'll look
around here.
Meredith: I'll take
the OR floor.

27:13.620 --> 27:14.790
I'll find Catherine.

27:14.790 --> 27:16.210
Page when you find him.

27:16.210 --> 27:18.080
[ Indistinct talking on P.A. ]

27:18.080 --> 27:19.250
Amelia:
Everything looks good.

27:19.250 --> 27:20.750
There was some bleeding,
but I packed it off.

27:20.750 --> 27:22.210
Ohh!

27:22.210 --> 27:23.620
The tumor's almost
fully exposed.

27:23.620 --> 27:24.960
Tom.

27:24.960 --> 27:26.540
You can do this.

27:26.540 --> 27:28.080
Ohh!

27:28.080 --> 27:29.620
[ Moaning ]

27:31.080 --> 27:32.420
Pickups.

27:32.420 --> 27:33.210
Probe.

27:34.960 --> 27:39.210
♪ Some folks are born
made to wave the flag ♪

27:39.210 --> 27:42.080
Continuing dissection.

27:42.080 --> 27:45.960
♪ They're red, white, and blue ♪

27:45.960 --> 27:50.540
♪♪

27:50.540 --> 27:52.790
[ Monitor alarm beeping ]
End-Tidal CO2 decreasing.

27:52.790 --> 27:53.750
BP just tanked.

27:53.750 --> 27:55.000
He's crashing.

27:55.000 --> 27:56.580
[ Alarm continues ]

27:56.580 --> 27:58.500
Dr. Koracick?

27:58.500 --> 28:00.420
♪ When the band plays... ♪

28:00.420 --> 28:02.920
Dr. Koracick?
Do I need to page someone else?

28:02.920 --> 28:04.620
[ Echoing ] Do I need to get
Dr. Shepherd in?

28:04.620 --> 28:05.710
Or call in Nelson?

28:05.710 --> 28:09.920
♪ They point the cannon
at you ♪

28:09.920 --> 28:11.500
[ Click ]
Tom.

28:11.500 --> 28:13.120
Listen to the sound
of my voice.

28:13.120 --> 28:14.460
Breathe in.

28:14.460 --> 28:15.620
Breathe out.

28:15.620 --> 28:17.420
Focus on the tools
in your hand.

28:17.420 --> 28:19.420
The feel of them,
the weight of them.

28:19.420 --> 28:20.960
There's a monitor
beeping in front of you.

28:20.960 --> 28:24.170
There is a patient on your
table who needs your help.

28:24.170 --> 28:27.210
This is a place that you have
been a thousand times.

28:27.210 --> 28:28.380
You can save him.

28:28.380 --> 28:32.040
♪ It ain't me, no ♪

28:32.040 --> 28:35.080
♪ I ain't no fortunate one ♪

28:35.080 --> 28:36.330
Air embolism.
Trendelenburg.

28:36.330 --> 28:38.500
Let's get his head
below his heart.

28:38.500 --> 28:40.420
Helm, I want you to irrigate.
Drown him in water.

28:40.420 --> 28:43.120
Knox, give him 100% O2, aspirate
through the central line.

28:43.120 --> 28:44.120
Now!

28:44.120 --> 28:46.000
Before he strokes out.
Come on.

28:46.000 --> 28:48.250
[ Alarm continues ]

28:48.250 --> 28:49.790
Let's turn him.
Let's turn him.
[ Softly ]
Come on, come on, come on.

28:51.250 --> 28:53.580
More, more.
Easy. Easy.

28:53.580 --> 28:54.830
Come on.

28:54.830 --> 28:56.710
Turn him. Turn him.

28:56.710 --> 28:58.460
Come on, buddy.
You can do it.

28:58.460 --> 29:00.750
[ Alarm continues ]

29:00.750 --> 29:01.710
Here we go.

29:01.710 --> 29:03.290
There!

29:03.290 --> 29:04.380
Gotcha.

29:04.380 --> 29:06.080
End-Tidal CO2's
coming back.

29:06.080 --> 29:07.120
[ Alarm stops ]
BP's rising.

29:07.120 --> 29:08.210
[ Sighs ]

29:08.210 --> 29:09.580
Taryn:
He's stabilizing.

29:10.790 --> 29:11.790
That was amazing.

29:11.790 --> 29:13.000
We're not out
of the woods yet.

29:13.000 --> 29:14.500
Let's get him back
into position. Let's go.

29:14.500 --> 29:16.040
♪ It ain't me ♪

29:16.040 --> 29:17.670
Easy.

29:17.670 --> 29:19.000
[ Paddles thump ]

29:19.000 --> 29:20.170
Owen: Tension pneumo,
maybe from intubation.

29:20.170 --> 29:21.750
I'm gonna need
a 14-gauge needle.

29:23.540 --> 29:25.500
Okay?

29:25.500 --> 29:27.000
Link: Alright, Vera.
I know it's hard,

29:27.000 --> 29:29.670
but you need
to try to relax, okay?

29:29.670 --> 29:30.960
Thank you.

29:30.960 --> 29:32.210
Vera,
on the count of three,

29:32.210 --> 29:33.790
I'm gonna insert
this needle, okay?

29:33.790 --> 29:35.710
One, two, three.

29:35.710 --> 29:37.920
[ Gasping ]

29:37.920 --> 29:38.830
Better?

29:38.830 --> 29:41.420
Vera! Are you okay?!

29:41.420 --> 29:42.540
I thought --

29:42.540 --> 29:43.750
[ Gasping continues ]

29:43.750 --> 29:45.580
I thought
I was losing you.

29:45.580 --> 29:47.880
♪ Ohh, much better ♪

29:47.880 --> 29:50.210
♪ Thank you ♪

29:50.210 --> 29:53.830
[ Crying ] Vera, even if you're
singing, I don't care.

29:53.830 --> 29:57.170
I just want you
to be okay.

29:57.170 --> 30:00.460
[ Off-key ]
♪ I love you ♪

30:00.460 --> 30:03.880
♪ More than words
can say ♪

30:07.080 --> 30:11.580
♪ I love you, too ♪

30:13.080 --> 30:15.580
[ Cellphone vibrates, chimes ]

30:15.580 --> 30:16.830
You gonna get that?

30:18.210 --> 30:19.960
I'm just enjoying
the moment.

30:21.670 --> 30:22.790
Oh, God.
What?

30:22.790 --> 30:24.330
It's happening.

30:24.330 --> 30:25.790
Ame-- Amelia.
It's -- It's happening.

30:25.790 --> 30:27.000
Go. Go, go, go.
We got this.

30:27.000 --> 30:28.080
Go!

30:29.670 --> 30:31.120
[ Door opens ]

30:32.790 --> 30:34.080
Are you okay?
Ohh!

30:34.080 --> 30:35.290
Oh, God. Oh, God.
What can I do?

30:35.290 --> 30:36.540
Where's Carina?

30:36.540 --> 30:38.380
She's on vacation with
her stupid girlfriend!

30:38.380 --> 30:39.790
[ Groans ]
That's okay.

30:39.790 --> 30:41.040
T-That's okay, right?

30:41.040 --> 30:42.120
No, no!
Nothing is okay!

30:42.120 --> 30:43.620
This whole time,
I've been thinking

30:43.620 --> 30:45.620
that if I could just give birth
to a healthy baby boy,

30:45.620 --> 30:47.460
that -- that -- that I would
have won some kind of race,

30:47.460 --> 30:48.710
just crossed
the finish line,

30:48.710 --> 30:50.420
but that's not where
the finish line is.

30:50.420 --> 30:51.500
I know.
There is no finish line.

30:51.500 --> 30:52.960
No,
there's no finish line!

30:52.960 --> 30:54.290
Once this baby is out
in the world,

30:54.290 --> 30:56.540
literally anything could
happen to him --

30:56.540 --> 30:59.290
cancer, car crash,
baseballs!

30:59.290 --> 31:01.290
Baseballs?
Ahh, make me feel better!

31:01.290 --> 31:02.500
Here.

31:02.500 --> 31:04.080
N-- ju-- ju-- ju--

31:04.080 --> 31:05.540
I-I'm freaking out!
What are we gonna do?!

31:05.540 --> 31:07.830
I don't know!
Stop yelling at me!

31:07.830 --> 31:09.670
[ Moaning ]

31:09.670 --> 31:10.540
[ Groans ]

31:10.540 --> 31:12.170
Aaaaaaaah!

31:14.790 --> 31:16.040
Richard: Scalpel.

31:16.040 --> 31:18.170
[ Monitor beeping ]

31:20.500 --> 31:21.960
You're late, Grey.

31:21.960 --> 31:24.000
I was just about to proceed
with the initial incision.

31:24.000 --> 31:25.540
Richard.

31:29.710 --> 31:31.420
You in or out?

31:31.420 --> 31:33.920
♪♪

31:33.920 --> 31:36.000
What's it gonna be?

31:37.420 --> 31:38.620
Let's see...

31:38.620 --> 31:41.080
♪♪

31:46.750 --> 31:49.920
Uh, uh...what surgery
are we performing?

31:49.920 --> 31:52.960
Um, the ex-lap.

31:52.960 --> 31:54.500
I'm glad to see you've
come to your senses.

31:54.500 --> 31:56.170
I could use the assist.

31:56.170 --> 31:57.580
[ Clears throat ]

32:00.170 --> 32:01.880
Okay, Richard.

32:01.880 --> 32:03.790
Uh, we need to, um...

32:03.790 --> 32:05.500
Hmm?
...ch-- check the, uh --

32:05.500 --> 32:08.460
the scalpel to make sure
it's been sterilized properly.

32:09.670 --> 32:11.920
Sterilized?
Of course it's sterilized.

32:13.750 --> 32:15.920
Richard, please.
No, no, no.

32:15.920 --> 32:17.420
I-- It needs
to be me, okay?

32:17.420 --> 32:19.540
I'm the only one who
can fix what's wrong.

32:19.540 --> 32:20.580
No, that is not true.

32:20.580 --> 32:22.380
Yes, it is!

32:22.380 --> 32:27.830
♪♪

32:27.830 --> 32:29.540
Richard, I can fix you.

32:30.790 --> 32:32.960
And I know I can fix you

32:32.960 --> 32:35.830
because you are the one
who taught me everything I know.

32:35.830 --> 32:38.920
And I'm not just
talking about surgery.

32:38.920 --> 32:41.040
You taught me how
to be a better person,

32:41.040 --> 32:42.920
how to be
a better mother.

32:42.920 --> 32:44.420
And what about
my children?

32:44.420 --> 32:46.460
I want them to grow up
and know who you are.

32:46.460 --> 32:47.330
Please.

32:48.880 --> 32:51.960
And I still have things
I need to learn.

32:51.960 --> 32:54.500
I need you. I'm not ready
to let you go yet.

32:56.380 --> 32:59.120
And I know
other people aren't, either.

33:03.210 --> 33:05.830
Hand me the scalpel,
please.

33:05.830 --> 33:13.790
♪♪

33:13.790 --> 33:15.000
Ellis.

33:17.750 --> 33:20.210
Something's...
wrong with me.

33:24.040 --> 33:25.710
Yes.

33:25.710 --> 33:27.040
It's okay.

33:27.040 --> 33:29.080
Take my hand, Richard.

33:31.830 --> 33:34.250
Let's go, now.
Come on.

33:34.250 --> 33:40.620
♪♪

33:40.620 --> 33:47.120
♪♪

33:47.120 --> 33:50.250
We removed the primary tumor
and the spinal metastasis,

33:50.250 --> 33:53.040
so he'll need some radiation of
the brain and the spinal cord,

33:53.040 --> 33:56.880
but as of now, Guthrie
is on the road to recovery.

33:56.880 --> 33:58.210
[ Sobbing ]

33:59.420 --> 34:00.620
Okay?

34:00.620 --> 34:01.830
Okay.

34:03.710 --> 34:05.670
Okay. Yeah.

34:05.670 --> 34:07.620
Hey, Doc, uh,
I don't know

34:07.620 --> 34:10.120
how we're ever gonna
be able to thank you.

34:10.120 --> 34:11.170
Mm.

34:13.330 --> 34:14.830
Dana: I thought
you couldn't do it.

34:14.830 --> 34:18.670
Still can't believe I --
I did.

34:18.670 --> 34:19.710
I'm sorry.

34:19.710 --> 34:21.960
No, no, no. No.

34:21.960 --> 34:23.500
And thank you.

34:23.500 --> 34:24.880
Thank you.

34:24.880 --> 34:25.880
Yeah.

34:26.830 --> 34:29.120
And Guthrie's, uh...

34:31.960 --> 34:33.330
It's a good name.

34:33.330 --> 34:34.670
[ Chuckles ]

34:34.670 --> 34:42.790
♪♪

34:42.790 --> 34:44.120
[ Groans ]

34:44.120 --> 34:45.710
Oh. Another one?
Is it bad?

34:45.710 --> 34:48.250
Ohh, you know when guys
get kicked in their...guys?

34:48.250 --> 34:49.620
[ Sighs ] How do you know
what that feels like?

34:49.620 --> 34:52.170
Everything goes black.
You want to throw up.

34:52.170 --> 34:54.250
Your whole body goes cold
all over because of the pain.

34:54.250 --> 34:55.080
That's exactly what
it feels like.

34:55.080 --> 34:57.000
Hoo! This is worse.

34:58.290 --> 34:59.620
We're gonna have a baby!

34:59.620 --> 35:01.000
We're gonna have a baby!

35:01.000 --> 35:02.420
Good news,
Dr. Shepherd!

35:02.420 --> 35:04.250
Based on the pelvic exam
and cervical length

35:04.250 --> 35:06.790
on ultrasound,
it looks like Braxton Hicks.

35:06.790 --> 35:08.710
Braxton Hicks?
False labor.

35:08.710 --> 35:10.540
When the uterus contracts
and relaxes.

35:10.540 --> 35:12.080
I know what
Braxton Hicks are.

35:12.080 --> 35:14.210
S-So, no baby?

35:14.210 --> 35:15.290
Not today.

35:15.290 --> 35:18.960
♪ We touch the fire ♪

35:18.960 --> 35:20.290
[ Door opens ]

35:20.290 --> 35:21.960
I really thought
this was real.

35:21.960 --> 35:23.170
[ Door closes ]
[ Sighs ] Same.

35:23.170 --> 35:26.500
♪ And we don't get burned ♪

35:26.500 --> 35:28.080
Suddenly,
they hurt less.

35:28.080 --> 35:30.330
[ Both laugh ]

35:30.330 --> 35:34.670
♪ It takes us higher ♪

35:34.670 --> 35:37.080
♪ And it's what we learn ♪

35:38.750 --> 35:43.330
♪ And it's what we le-e-e-arn ♪

35:43.330 --> 35:47.420
♪ It's everything
that we cannot see ♪

35:47.420 --> 35:50.830
♪ It's the mystery ♪

35:50.830 --> 35:52.000
♪ Ohh ♪

35:52.000 --> 35:53.790
[ Sighs ]

35:53.790 --> 35:55.540
♪ It's going to be ♪

35:55.540 --> 35:56.790
Thank you.

35:56.790 --> 35:59.000
♪ It's going to be,
it's going to be ♪

35:59.000 --> 36:00.420
Tom, I'm...

36:00.420 --> 36:03.210
♪ It's everything
that we cannot see ♪

36:03.210 --> 36:04.750
I'm so sorry.

36:04.750 --> 36:07.000
'Cause you've had more
than enough pain.

36:07.000 --> 36:10.420
♪ Ohh, it's going to be,
it's going to be ♪

36:10.420 --> 36:12.500
You've taken away more
than you've caused.

36:12.500 --> 36:15.880
♪ It's going to be,
it's going to be ♪

36:15.880 --> 36:19.420
♪ Oh, oh, oh, oh ♪

36:19.420 --> 36:23.330
♪ Oh, oh, oh, oh ♪

36:23.330 --> 36:27.000
♪ Oh, oh, oh, oh ♪

36:27.000 --> 36:36.540
♪♪

36:36.540 --> 36:38.500
[ Indistinct talking on TV ]

36:38.500 --> 36:40.250
Jo: Hey!
Hi.

36:40.250 --> 36:41.670
What do you want
to watch?

36:41.670 --> 36:43.960
Uh, I'm going back
to the hospital.

36:43.960 --> 36:45.540
Oh, did they
extend your shift?

36:45.540 --> 36:47.540
[ Sighs ] Uh, to sleep.

36:48.880 --> 36:50.920
And I-I-I don't want
to be a fish.

36:50.920 --> 36:52.880
A [Chuckles] fish?

36:52.880 --> 36:54.750
Levi, what are you
talking about?

36:54.750 --> 36:56.460
House guests and fish.

36:56.460 --> 36:58.420
After three days,
they both start to stink.

36:58.420 --> 37:00.250
My mom taught me that.

37:00.250 --> 37:02.380
Okay, your mom also
taught you

37:02.380 --> 37:04.120
to hide the best parts
of yourself.

37:04.120 --> 37:05.710
Why would you ever
listen to her?

37:05.710 --> 37:08.380
Well, you keep telling me
how great I had it at my mom's

37:08.380 --> 37:10.580
and spent the whole day
yelling at me.

37:10.580 --> 37:11.880
[ Zipper closes ]

37:11.880 --> 37:15.080
Yeah, because you weren't
doing a good job.

37:15.080 --> 37:16.790
I'm not gonna change
the way that I work

37:16.790 --> 37:18.670
just because
we're friends.

37:18.670 --> 37:21.500
I know that I wasn't
an attending when we met,

37:21.500 --> 37:23.290
but I am now, and that means
I'm gonna snap at you

37:23.290 --> 37:24.620
when you get things
wrong.

37:24.620 --> 37:26.290
Otherwise, you're never
gonna become the surgeon

37:26.290 --> 37:27.960
that you should be.

37:27.960 --> 37:30.170
And you're not a fish.

37:30.170 --> 37:31.670
You're probably
the main reason

37:31.670 --> 37:34.120
that I'm at all sane
right now.

37:35.080 --> 37:37.750
So...

37:37.750 --> 37:39.080
what are
we watching tonight?

37:41.250 --> 37:42.710
Something with hot guys?

37:42.710 --> 37:44.250
Ohh! Sold!

37:44.250 --> 37:46.330
[ Coco Bans' "Pray" plays ]

37:46.330 --> 37:47.710
Okay.

37:47.710 --> 37:51.250
[ Indistinct talking on P.A. ]

37:51.250 --> 37:53.540
Hey. I'm gonna
go get the kids.

37:53.540 --> 37:57.210
I would sing with you
if I had to.

37:57.210 --> 37:59.460
[ Chuckles ]
But I really can't sing.

37:59.460 --> 38:02.080
[ Laughs ] What?

38:02.080 --> 38:04.580
♪ Though you're still
not around me ♪

38:04.580 --> 38:05.750
Come on.

38:05.750 --> 38:07.330
Come here.

38:07.330 --> 38:08.580
Come on.

38:08.580 --> 38:09.750
Come on.

38:09.750 --> 38:13.380
♪ Oh, I went down on my knees
to pray ♪

38:13.380 --> 38:17.420
♪ I asked the Lord
to accept you ♪

38:17.420 --> 38:20.830
♪ Though you're still
not around me ♪

38:20.830 --> 38:22.330
[ Exhales deeply ]

38:22.330 --> 38:23.670
Screw the plans.

38:23.670 --> 38:25.290
Huh? What?

38:25.290 --> 38:27.000
Screw the plans.

38:27.000 --> 38:30.460
♪ I'll keep moving ♪

38:30.460 --> 38:32.710
I want to be
married to you.

38:32.710 --> 38:34.080
As soon as possible.

38:34.080 --> 38:35.000
Mm.

38:35.000 --> 38:37.790
♪ I'll get through this ♪

38:37.790 --> 38:39.710
Let's do it.

38:39.710 --> 38:41.080
Let's do it
this weekend.

38:41.080 --> 38:44.290
♪ Times get tough at times,
I'll admit it ♪

38:44.290 --> 38:48.420
♪ It looks like I'm drowning,
like I'm sinking in it ♪

38:48.420 --> 38:50.880
♪ But I won't let you down ♪

38:50.880 --> 38:54.710
♪ I'm not giving up tonight ♪

38:56.290 --> 38:58.670
I love you, Teddy.
I love you.

38:58.670 --> 39:00.170
Meredith: There are certain
moments in my life

39:00.170 --> 39:02.540
that I wish I could relive --

39:02.540 --> 39:06.460
first day of internship,
first solo surgery,

39:06.460 --> 39:09.420
first time I held
my children in my arms.

39:09.420 --> 39:11.380
Oh, oh, where am I?

39:11.380 --> 39:12.880
Maggie: You're in
the hospital, Richard.

39:12.880 --> 39:14.120
What? Seattle Grace?

39:15.790 --> 39:17.170
Grey Sloan.

39:19.250 --> 39:21.670
Oh, well, um,
um, send for the interns.

39:21.670 --> 39:24.210
I-I want to start
rounds right away.

39:24.210 --> 39:27.960
Adele will kill me if
I'm late for dinner again.

39:27.960 --> 39:30.960
The last lucid conversation
I had with my mother.

39:30.960 --> 39:34.500
♪ You'd know how to
make this go away ♪

39:34.500 --> 39:35.620
Okay.

39:36.580 --> 39:37.580
Mom.

39:39.040 --> 39:40.670
Hey.

39:40.670 --> 39:42.250
[ Voice breaking ]
I can't do this.

39:42.250 --> 39:43.670
Yeah, you can.

39:43.670 --> 39:44.790
We can.

39:44.790 --> 39:46.500
Alright?
We're gonna fix him.

39:46.500 --> 39:47.960
We're gonna figure it out.
I'm right here with you.

39:47.960 --> 39:49.460
Jackie!
I know.

39:49.460 --> 39:50.960
But for every one of those...

39:50.960 --> 39:52.580
[ Sobbing ]
I'm gonna fix him.

39:52.580 --> 39:54.330
...there's one I wish I could
forget or do differently.

39:54.330 --> 39:58.420
♪ Tonight ♪

39:58.420 --> 40:00.210
Those are the moments
that keep me up at night.

40:00.210 --> 40:01.750
♪ I'll admit it ♪

40:01.750 --> 40:05.380
♪ It looks like I'm drowning,
like I'm sinking in it ♪

40:05.380 --> 40:08.250
♪ But I won't let you down ♪

40:08.250 --> 40:11.500
♪ 'Cause you're here
with me tonight ♪

40:13.460 --> 40:15.710
Did Bailey tell you
to come here, kick me out?

40:15.710 --> 40:20.040
♪ Oh, oh, oh ♪

40:20.040 --> 40:22.500
What have you thought of
that we haven't?

40:22.500 --> 40:23.620
What do you mean?

40:23.620 --> 40:25.120
Are you going to pretend
you're not in here

40:25.120 --> 40:26.380
trying to figure out
what's wrong with Richard?

40:30.620 --> 40:32.080
[ Sighs ]

40:32.080 --> 40:33.540
I'm just trying to
go over some of these points

40:33.540 --> 40:35.830
'cause just --
it doesn't make sense.

40:35.830 --> 40:36.880
It doesn't.

40:37.960 --> 40:39.710
So, what do you have?

40:39.710 --> 40:41.000
Because we're not leaving here
until we figure this out.

40:41.000 --> 40:42.540
Really?

40:42.540 --> 40:44.790
Thought I was supposed to, uh,
go home, get some rest.

40:44.790 --> 40:46.880
♪ I won't let you down ♪

40:46.880 --> 40:48.790
[ Sighs ]
Are you with me or not?

40:48.790 --> 40:51.120
♪ Tonight ♪

40:51.120 --> 40:53.750
Okay. This is
what I got so far.

40:53.750 --> 40:56.290
[ Sighs ]

40:56.290 --> 40:59.960
♪ Oh, I pray ♪

40:59.960 --> 41:03.420
And no matter what I do, they
keep coming back to haunt me.

41:03.420 --> 41:07.580
♪ 'Cause you're here
with me tonight ♪

41:07.580 --> 41:10.080
♪♪

41:18.380 --> 41:26.790
♪♪

41:26.790 --> 41:35.380
♪♪

41:35.380 --> 41:43.210
